@NODE Page_1 "About TMA"

****************************************************************************

                               @{b}About TMA@{ub}

****************************************************************************


        TMA was developed on :-

        ... via WorkBench 3.0
        Amiga A1200
        Blitz Basic 2
        Deluxe Paint III & IV
        AudioMaster II
        OctaMED Pro V3

        Playtesting on :-

        Two Amiga A1200 2Mb CHIP, ROM V39.107
        Amiga A500 Plus 1Mb CHIP, ROM V37.350


        I created @{b}TMA@{ub} after noticing a severe lack of
        non-linear games on the Amiga games market. My main influence
        comes from the @{b}Ultimate Play the Game@{ub} series, and
        although @{b}TMA@{ub} is nowhere near as good as these, I think
        it fills a gap.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Page_2 "Instructions"

****************************************************************************

                              @{b}Instructions@{ub}

****************************************************************************


        The aim of the game is simple. Guide your ship through the
        various zones collecting power crystals and avoiding the aliens.
        Coloured passes will appear if you need them, enabling you to
        pass through the relevant forcefields.

        PAUSE:      SPACE BAR
        ABORT:      SPACE BAR then ESCAPE

        @{b}HINTS & TIPS@{ub}

        a) Collect a lazer as soon as possible (preferably the twin
           speed)

        b) Keys give access to other zones

        c) Only collect extra ammo or energy if desparately needed

        d) If it moves, shoot it

        e) As this is a @{" unregistered "     LINK Page_5}version, don't go through the
           exit, which is RIGHT and UP from the start


@ENDNODE

