@NODE Page_5 "Shareware Notice"

****************************************************************************

                           @{b}Shareware Notice@{ub}

****************************************************************************


        THIS IS AN UNREGISTERED VERSION AND FEATURES AN ANNOYING
        SHAREWARE MESSAGE AFTER EACH GAME.

        If, after you have played TMA, you feel that you like it, maybe
        alot or maybe just a bit, and want the whole game, the
        instructions are simple. Just send a Cheque or Postal Order
        for only Ł5.00, payable to HOWARD WILSHER and send it to the
        following address:-

        @{b}Howard Wilsher
        58 Hildreth Road
        Prestwood
        Great Missenden
        Bucks
        HP16 OLY
        England@{ub}

        The advantages with registering are:-

        You get the full, completable game (really!) with end sequence
        4 Game variations
        Fully personalised
        Hard Disk Installer
        Exit to Workbench option
        Recieve information about forthcoming CLEAR products
        Technical Helpline via Telephone
        Half price TMA AGA, see @{" TMA AGA " LINK Page_6}

        THE FULL VERSION OF TMA WILL BE SUPPLIED ON 2 MAXELL BRANDED
        DISKS, AND WILL FEATURE NUMEROUS OTHER MINOR ADDITIONS AS
        WELL AS THOSE LISTED.

        When you register, and you wish to take advantage of the
        Hard Disk install, please give information on the EXACT path
        you are going to install TMA, i.e. DH1:TMA/ or Games:TMA/. If you
        don't give this information we cannot give you the Hard Disk
        install program, and there is no or little way you the end user
        can install it him or herself (see, I'm not sexist!).


@ENDNODE

@NODE Page_6 "TMA AGA by Howard Wilsher"

****************************************************************************

                                @{b}TMA AGA@{ub}

****************************************************************************


        It can't be true??? YES it is. CLEAR will be doing a special AGA
        version of TMA. This will (obviously) include enhancements such as
        better graphics, new sound fx, different tune(s), better control-
        system, and the list could go on (but it won't)
        More information will become available soon. When you
        register standard TMA, please state if you have an AGA machine
        so when the AGA version becomes available, we can notify you.
        Also, if you have already have a @{" registered copy " LINK Page_5} of TMA, you
        can get the AGA version for @{b}half price@{ub}, which will be Ł2.50

        The AGA version will only be tested on an A1200, so we cannot be
        sure if it works an, for instance A4000/030.
@ENDNODE
